Acting Director General of the State Security Agency, Loyiso Jafta, has been replaced as his term has lapsed. (Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Acting Director General of the State Security Agency, Loyiso Jafta, has been replaced as his term has come to an end. The agency has appointed Ambassador Gab Msimanga to act in the position. There has been public tension between Jafta and State Security Minister Ayanda Dlodlo. READ: WATCH: State capture inquiry hears SSA-related evidence Most notable was when Dlodlo attempted to stop Jafta from giving evidence before the State Capture Commission of Inquiry about issues that concerned him at the SSA. Dlodlo said he had undermined her authority. Jafta has been acting in the position since 2018.